===Usual types of ambulances and their staff===
Spanish EMS is a physician led system with physicians, emergency nurses and technicians in the field. It's a two-tiered response system (Advanced Life Support with physicians and nurses,<ref>Advanced life support units in Spain: the situation in 2008 E E.Pesqueira Alonso , P.  Juliano Izquierdo http://www.semes.org/revista/vol21_4/6_ing.pdf</ref> and Basic Life Support with technicians).

